### doPRE() {#a386589bdd2443917d5976cf9dc0b413e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void RISCVInsertVSETVLI::doPRE (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> &amp; MBB)</>}>
Perform simple partial redundancy elimination of the VSETVLI instructions we&#39;re about to insert by looking for cases where we can PRE from the beginning of one block to the end of one of its predecessors.

Specifically, this is geared to catch the common case of a fixed length vsetvl in a single block loop when it could execute once in the preheader instead.
